The paper discusses a session types discipline for a calculus that features communication and runtime adaptation, which suggests that it could belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the challenges of context-aware and adaptable distributed systems, which could place it in the Software Engineering (cs.SE) or Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. Finally, the paper presents an example of a mechanism for enforcing fault-tolerant applications, which could relate to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category.
